<h1><span id="Traxler_Counterattack">Traxler Counterattack</span></h1>
<h3><span id="4._...Bc5">4. ...Bc5</span></h3>
<dl><dd>The move that signifies the Traxler Counterattack or sometimes known as the Wilkes-Barre Variation. This can quickly lead to mate with the queen.</dd>
<dd>This bold move ignores White's attack on f7 and can lead to wild play as Black can try a bishop sacrifice on f2 if White plays Nxf7. Instead, White will often prefer Bxf7+.</dd></dl>
